<item>
            <title>[OAK-546] Query: unexpected result on negative limit / offset</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-546</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, running a query with limit of -1 never returns any rows, the same as when using limit = 0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Either the query engine should fail with a negative limit or offset (IllegalArgumentException), or it should ignore negative values (unlimited result rows for limit, probably no offset for offset = -1).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would prefer IllegalArgumentException, but I can also live with -1 = unlimited, at least for &quot;limit&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
